comments: I think the easiest part was identifying which prefix (gafi, buvi, xeti, wopi) signifed which shape, but the xou/she ending was a lot more difficult. Certain colours seemed to mean either 'xou' or 'she' depending on the shape. I also noticed some pronunciation differences but didn't really get a handle on it. I was obviously missing something as during the exchange part at the end we were often picking the correct shape but wrong colour - as a given word could refer to 2 or 3 different possibilities.
